      "question": "Show that the number $7 \times 11 \times 13 + 13$ is a composite number without performing the actual multiplication.",
      "answer": "The expression is composite because it has factors other than 1 and itself.",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Factor out the common term $13$ from the expression $7 \times 11 \times 13 + 13$.",
          "Observe that the resulting expression is a product of two integers greater than $1$, proving it is composite."
        ],
        "derivation": "$7 \times 11 \times 13 + 13 = 13(7 \times 11 + 1) \\\\ = 13(77 + 1) \\\\ = 13 \times 78 \\\\ = 13 \times 13 \times 6$"
      },
